.SS Net
.PP
Creates a block which displays the upload and download throughput for a
network interface.
Units are by default in bytes per second (kB/s, MB/s, etc), but the
`use_bits' flag can be set to \f[C]true\f[R] to convert the units to bps
(little b).
.PP
\f[C]bitrate\f[R] for wired devices requires \f[C]ethtool\f[R] to be
installed.
\f[C]ssid\f[R] requires one of \f[C]iw\f[R], \f[C]wpa_cli\f[R],
\f[C]nm-cli\f[R] or \f[C]iwctl\f[R] to be installed.
.SS Examples
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
[[block]]
block = \[dq]net\[dq]
device = \[dq]wlp2s0\[dq]
ssid = true
signal_strength = true
ip = true
speed_up = false
graph_up = true
interval = 5
use_bits = false
\f[R]
